<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="627" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d627">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2421</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Treasury</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MWG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">McAdoo</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-10">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1916</hi>
                                    </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received April
                                    12</hi>.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to a memorandum dated the
                                28th ultimo of Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">Charles A.
                                    Holder</persName>, foreign trade adviser,<note n="1" xml:id="d627fn1">Not printed.</note> I have the honor to
                                transmit herewith for the information of your Department, a copy of
                                a letter this day addressed to collectors of customs in whose
                                districts customs-bonded manufacturing warehouses are located,
                                instructing them relative to the issuance of certificates as to the
                                contents of packages of manufactured tobacco exported from such
                                    warehouses.<note n="1" xml:id="d627fn2">Not printed.</note> By
                                direction of the Secretary.</p>
                            <p>Respectfully,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MWP1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. P. Malburn</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary</hi>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>